    "version": "0.99.207",
    "date": "2026-06-14",
    "body": "### Changed\n- **GEODE.md SOUL doc rebalanced toward behavioral identity + the behavioral half wired into the system prompt** (PR-GEODE-SOUL; operator-directed, benchmarked against the Fable 5 system prompt + frontier agent-identity docs). GEODE.md is the Tier-0 SOUL injected into every LLM context, but it was ~85% architecture reference and ~15% behavior — it had no voice/tone, anti-sycophancy, refusal-tone, persistence, or output-norm guidance, the half every frontier system prompt is mostly made of. Added (second person): a **Voice & Conduct** section (direct/concise, warm-without-flattery, honest-over-agreeable, no-slop), **Operating Principles** (persistence \"keep going until resolved, don't guess\", progress-narration, plus the prior evidence/bias/second-opinion/degrade principles), a refusal-philosophy line in **RUNTIME CANNOT** (decline like a person, proportionate, offer an alternative), a tool-use philosophy + a by-example \"How you act\" block in **Tool Use**. Compressed the Architecture section (was 35% of the file, deep wiring constants) to a capability summary, keeping the honest isolation-boundary contract and the grounded model table; moved the \"English in LLM-context files\" authoring rule to CLAUDE.md. **Wiring (the load-bearing part)**: `core/agent/system_prompt.py::_build_identity_context` (G1) parses GEODE.md by EXACT section header — it injected only `Core Principles + RUNTIME CANNOT + Defaults`. Repointed it to the BEHAVIORAL sections (`Voice & Conduct + Operating Principles + RUNTIME CANNOT`) and dropped the numeric `Defaults` (reference, not identity) from the system prompt, so the new conduct guidance actually reaches the model; also strip cross-reference blockquotes from the injection. Guard: `tests/core/agent/test_geode_soul_g1_behavioral.py` pins that the behavioral sections reach G1 (a future header rename can't silently disconnect the SOUL again).\n\n### Fixed\n- **GEODE.md internal numeric contradictions corrected against code** (same PR): tool count `59` → **60** (`core/tools/definitions.json`), hook events `81` → **62** (the file also said 62 elsewhere; `HookEvent` enum = 62), Lane global concurrency `8` → **50** (`DEFAULT_GLOBAL_CONCURRENCY`), SubAgent timeout `120s` → **600s** (`core/agent/worker.py` / `sub_agent.py` default, clamped 10..3600) — a SOUL doc injected into every context must not carry wrong constants (\"measured values only\"). Removed the stale LangGraph-era `Node contract` / `Reducer fields (Annotated[list, operator.add])` conventions — the core runs the AgenticLoop, not a graph (cf. PR-LANGGRAPH-PURGE). Also corrected the safety-contract descriptions to match code (Codex review, 3 rounds): `DANGEROUS_TOOLS` = `run_bash` + `computer` (not `delegate_task`, which the old table wrongly listed); the permission tiers now state that approval is decided at runtime by the approval gate from `hitl_level` + standing Always-grants + read-only detection (mode-dependent, not a fixed threshold), rather than overclaiming \"always requires HITL\"; IPC = hitl=2 (no headless deny filter); headless DAEMON/SCHEDULER deny `run_bash` + `delegate_task` (`_HEADLESS_DENIED_TOOLS`, a separate list from DANGEROUS_TOOLS). A SOUL injected into every context must not assert a stronger safety contract than the runtime enforces."
