    "body": "### Removed\n- **Vestigial LangGraph dependency + dead graph-runtime surface purged** (PR-LANGGRAPH-PURGE; operator-directed). The in-tree analysis graph (the Game-IP `StateGraph` pipeline) was removed in **v0.99.149** — since then GEODE core's runtime has been the `AgenticLoop` (`while tool_use`), not a LangGraph `StateGraph`, and `langgraph` was fully vestigial: a single `TYPE_CHECKING`-only `CompiledStateGraph` import typing a `compile_graph()` stub that only `raise`d, plus a never-non-None `_compiled_graph`, two unused properties (`thread_config` \"LangGraph thread config\", `checkpoint_db` \"MemorySaver fallback in compile_graph\"), the `build_thread_config` RunnableConfig wrapper (no production caller), a dead `enable_checkpoint` create() param, and two LangGraph warning-suppression filters. Removed all of it: the `langgraph>=1.1.0` dependency (+ `langgraph-checkpoint{,-sqlite}` deptry entries + the `langgraph.*` / `langchain_core.*` mypy overrides — `langchain_core` was only a transitive of langgraph), `compile_graph` / `_compiled_graph` / `thread_config` / `checkpoint_db` / `build_thread_config` / `enable_checkpoint`, and the LangGraph entries in `suppress_noisy_warnings` (now a documented no-op hook). `uv.lock` drops the whole langgraph/langchain tree (ormsgpack, uuid-utils, tenacity, xxhash). `build_session_key` (the real session util) and `settings.checkpoint_db` (config field) are kept. Exposed-surface docs reframed to the AgenticLoop: README LangGraph badge removed (the `while(tool_use)-agentic loop` badge already names the engine), `CLAUDE.md` \"built on LangGraph\" → AgenticLoop + the stale `graph.py` cascading-update row dropped, the `external-references` \"direct foundation of GEODE's graph.py\" rows removed (no `graph.py` exists). mypy 487 files clean + full gates green without langgraph, proving the dependency was dead. The LangGraph history lives in git + this entry. Codex review surfaced more dead graph-state surface, also removed: `GeodeRuntime.get_tool_state_injection` (graph-state tool injection) + the now-orphaned `set/get_async_tool_executor` contextvar in `core/tools/registry.py` (the AgenticLoop uses `ToolExecutor` directly, never that contextvar), `build_subagent_thread_config`, and the stale `LangGraph` references in `AGENTS.md`, `NOTICE`, and the committed `llms-full.txt`. `task_system.has_failed_dependency`'s \"LangGraph integration\" docstring was reframed. (The `site/src/data/geode/categories.ts` \"pipeline\" portfolio category + the orphaned `pipeline-nodes.ts` diagram still describe the removed router→synthesizer pipeline — flagged as a portfolio-narrative decision, not mechanically rewritten.)"
