    "version": "0.99.202",
    "date": "2026-06-14",
    "body": "### Added\n- **config.toml is now a complete surface — 48 previously env-only fields mapped** (PR-OBS-LOGGING-CONFIG Phase C; pre-v1.0 config-centralization convergence, plan `docs/plans/2026-06-14-obs-logging-config-convergence.md`). `core/config/__init__.py` `_TOML_TO_SETTINGS` only mapped a subset of `Settings` fields, so operators could set the rest only via env vars — `cost_limit_usd`, `hitl_level`, the `scheduler_*` / `session_*` / `notification_*` / `webhook_*` / `gateway_*` sections, the `llm_*_timeout` pool knobs, `agentic_effort`, `computer_use_enabled`, and more silently had no `[section] key` route. All 76 `Settings` fields now resolve from `config.toml` (73 mapped + 3 credential keys intentionally env-only via `_TOML_ENV_ONLY_FIELDS` — API keys never belong in a committed config). Frontier parity: Hermes maps its full key set through YAML. Guard: `tests/core/config/test_config_centralization.py` pins drift-proof coverage (every non-secret field mapped, no stale/duplicate targets).\n- **Structured JSON file logging — `GEODE_LOG_FORMAT=json`** (PR-OBS-LOGGING-CONFIG Phase A). `core/observability/logging_config.py` gains a `_JsonFormatter` (one `{ts, level, logger, msg}` object per line, machine-filterable) selectable per the env var; the stderr console stays human-readable in both modes (openclaw `console=pretty` / `file=jsonl` parity). Default `text` preserves the legacy format. `trace_id` / `span_id` are reserved header slots for the follow-up OTel trace↔log coupling.\n- **config value validators reject malformed boot config** (PR-OBS-LOGGING-CONFIG Phase D). `core/config/_settings.py` now validates the `llm_*_timeout` + `*_interval_s` durations (`> 0`, else a 0s busy-loop) and `agentic_effort` — previously only `credential_source` was checked, so a typo'd `config.toml` surfaced as a mid-call provider 400 instead of a clear boot error. The effort validator accepts the **full per-provider union the picker can persist** (`AGENTIC_EFFORTS` = Anthropic `low..xhigh` + OpenAI `none`/`minimal` + GLM `disabled`/`enabled`); a narrower set would reject a valid config the picker itself wrote (e.g. gpt-5.5 + `none`) and brick the next `Settings()` load (caught in Codex review). A drift test pins `AGENTIC_EFFORTS` to `core.cli.effort_picker`'s union. (The `temperature_*` fields already carried native `Field(ge=0.0, le=2.0)` constraints; no redundant validator added.) Guard: `tests/core/config/test_config_centralization.py`.\n\n### Infrastructure\n- **Automatic secret redaction at the logging formatter — log-leak guard** (PR-OBS-LOGGING-CONFIG Phase A, P0 security). `redact_secrets` was call-site-only, so any of the ~240 logging call sites could leak an `sk-ant-…` / `xoxb-…` token to stderr or the rotating file. A `_RedactingTextFormatter` now scrubs the FINAL rendered line on **both** the stream and file handlers (and inside `_JsonFormatter`), making redaction unmissable — frontier parity (openclaw/hermes redact at the logger/formatter level, not per-call). Guard: `tests/core/observability/test_logging_redaction.py` (4 tests, incl. end-to-end emit→handler-output).\n- **committed site version drift ratchet — llms.txt / llms-full.txt / sot.ts** (PR-OBS-LOGGING-CONFIG Phase L; operator-directed). The committed `site/public/llms.txt` + `llms-full.txt` header (`Version vX.Y.Z`) **and** `site/src/data/geode/sot.ts` had drifted 12 versions behind `pyproject.toml` (v0.99.189 committed) — the deploy pipeline rebuilds them on every Pages deploy but never commits the refresh back, so the repo's own SoT misreported its version (CLAUDE.md \"dual SoT without drift invariant\"). `scripts/check_llms_version.py` pins all three committed version tokens to `pyproject.toml` (`--fix` resyncs the two llms headers; `sot.ts` is regenerated by `sync-stats`, so the guard checks it but defers the fix to that tool — closing the false pass where llms reads current while `sot.ts`/`changelog.ts` stay stale, found in Codex review). Wired as a ci.yml ratchet so a future version bump can't silently drift; the committed `sot.ts` + `changelog.ts` were resynced via `sync-stats`. CLAUDE.md docs-sync table documents the resync step. Guard: `tests/scripts/test_check_llms_version.py`."
